# ğŸ§  **Key Features (Explained in My Point of View)**

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Document Understanding Pipeline

I designed a complete DU flow:
Digitize Document â†’ Load Taxonomy â†’ Data Extraction Scope â†’ Regex Based Extractor

### DU handles:
- Claim ID  
- Member ID  
- Patient Name  
- Provider Name  
- Provider NPI  
- Service Dates  
- CPT/HCPCS Code  
- ICD-10 Code  
- Units  
- Line Amount  
- Total Amount  

The extraction is driven by a custom **Taxonomy.json** (included in repo).

### Why DU?
Because healthcare PDFs come in different formats.  
DU + Regex gives accurate, structured extraction even from scanned PDFs.

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Business Rule Validation Engine

After extraction, I created a validation block that applies healthcare rules such as:

### âœ” NPI Format Check  
Must be exactly 10 digits

### âœ” ICD-10 Format Check  
[A-Z][0-9][0-9][A-Z0-9]{0,4}

### âœ” Required Field Check  
- Claim ID  
- Member ID  
- Provider NPI  
- Total Amount  
- Service Dates  

### âœ” Date Range Check  
ServiceDateFrom â‰¤ ServiceDateTo

### âœ” Amount Check  
Sum of line-level charges must equal header TotalChargeAmount.

### âœ” Error Aggregation  
If any rule fails â†’ all messages are collected into `ErrorMessages`.

This creates an audit trail that healthcare payers and compliance teams expect.

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Action Center Human Review

For every invalid claim:

- A **Form Task** is created
- The form automatically displays:
  - Claim ID (read-only)
  - Error Messages (read-only)
  - Provider NPI
  - Resolution (Approve / Fix & Resubmit / Reject)
  - Reviewer Comments

### Why Action Center?  
Healthcare claims require **human review** when rules fail.  
Rather than rejecting automatically, I give the reviewer a chance to approve or correct.

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Excel Output Generation

The bot produces two files:
Output/
â”‚â”€â”€ ValidClaims.xlsx â†’ Clean, validated claims
â”‚â”€â”€ ErrorClaims.xlsx â†’ Invalid claims before human review
These files give a clear comparison of:

- What passed
- What failed
- Why it failed (detailed error messages)

